The last couple days I've been in New Brunswick and the Toronto area speaking out against Justin Trudeau’s unfair new carbon tax. While he makes it harder and harder to get by, I want to help you get ahead. That’s why my first act as Prime Minister will be to get rid of it.pic.twitter.com/P43RLiQqzz

Principale leçon de ce désastre: découle entièrement d’une tentative cynique d’acheter qq votes au Qc. Ça renforce ma croyance de faire de la politique sur des principes et bonnes politiques pour TOUS les Canadiens, gagne ou perd. Je ne vais pas vendre mon âme pour le pouvoir.https://twitter.com/RadioCanadaInfo/status/1113202435164651520 …

The main lesson of this disaster is that it derives entirely from a shortsighted and cynical attempt to buy a few votes in Quebec. It reinforces my belief that politics should be about principles and good policies for ALL Canadians. Win or lose. I won’t sell my soul for power.https://twitter.com/CTVNews/status/1113207751621132288 …
